spanGrp.span: They used to tell about the twins.
One time they lived on top of a hill.
Ciinąk kąnąkiregi eeja aire ciiregi hagoreižą hagoreižą wąąkjaane hinųkra hakaraikižu?? roogųire.
Where they lived, a man and his wife wanted (something).
ciną́k kaną́kiregi eeja ciiregi (ha)goréi(ž)ą (ha)goréi(ž)ą wąąk jané hinúkra (ha)karáikižų ?? rogų́įne
something missing at the end ("'aire"?) -- LP: Added aire after the first eeja, but at the end it's very unclear.
Heesge eeja nįge howarairegi nįįwiceja nįįsge eeja hahiiregi eeja eeja ciiporoke kiikʼųire.
They went someplace and when they got there they made themselves a wigwam.
heske eeja nig(e) (h)owaraíregi nįį(hi)chécha niské eeja (ha)hiregi eeja eeja cipóroke kik'ų́įne
removed one "nįįsge" -- LP: Ok, also removed on or.
Hegų hagoreižą hagoreižą eegi hocįcį <<ui>xųnųįkra> nųųpįwiže.
One time, they had two boys.
Hagoreižą hižą tʼeežegają haakja eeja nįįʔąp nįįʔąp kirijeegiže.
One time, one died and came back to life.
(ha)goréi(ž)ą hi(ž)ą́ t'éže gajá hakjá eeja nį'ąp nį'ą́p kirijége že
Hagoreižą waką xete hanįakiriire anąga hagoreižą
One time they brought back a big snake [and one time ...]
woohąiregi hegų hagoreižą hija hakeregi hegų xʼookenąąka nąąǧirairegi giʔasregi hegų haakja hakarairegi žeegų.
one time when they boiled it they set it there and their parents were frightened and ran away to where they came from.
wohaínegi hegu (ha)goréi(ž)ą hijá hakerégi hegu x'óke nąąka naǧírairegi gi'ázregi hegu hakjá (ha)karairegi žegu
Žeegų hocįcįnąąka hegų hija howe hegų hija howe ųųnąąk.
One time as they were there,
tee xee xeeʔuk nįįsge hihakeja tee wanįk hoomąižą eeja hirahiire tee.
kind of on the side of a hill they came upon a bird's nest.
te xee xée'uk ni(ske) (hi)hagéja te wanį́k homaí(ž)a eja hirahíre te
Xųnųįka wanįk xųnųįknąąkre eešąną hija ųųnąąk.
Those little birds were alone there.
xunų́įka wanį́k xunų́įng nąągre éšaną hija 'únąąk
They asked them "What are your names?"
Hižą eegi wąąnįhega hįįgairawiže eegi hegų Wąąre Eegają wąągają hegų hagoreižą hegų.
One said "We are called War Holler" and he hollered one time.
hižą́ egi wáanihega hįgaírawiže egi hegu waané egaja wąągáją hegu (ha)goréi(ž)ą hegu
Mąąxi hegų wąąkregi hegų jiinąkjee hagoreižą.
Hirarexjįgają hegų kʼoirenąga hegų jąąjąpire žeegų hagoreižą.
It thundered and there was lightning.
hiraréxjįgaja hegu k'óireąga hegu jąją́pire žegu (ha)goréi(ž)ą
Hegų eegi hiraicera teʔe howare žeegų.
Hegų mąįtajewehixjį žeegų eeja kiri hegų.
It was extremely windy and he returned.
BO added that 'eeja, makes more sense
Wanįkįk xųnųįknąka Wąąnįhega higairegi heesge hawaʔų waʔųže.
That little bird [was] called War Holler that's why he did it.
wanįkį́ng xunų́įg nąka wáanihega (hi)gáire(gi) hesk(e) (ha)wa'ų́ wa'ų́že
Eegi eeja ųųnąąkʼų hagoreižą žige eeja harukąnąkregi nįįra howaraire.
Again one time they went down to the river.
egi eeja 'ų́nąąk'ų (ha)goréi(ž)ą žigé eeja harukanąkregi nįįną (ho)waraire
One time they went under water.
Haʔųhahiiregają tee horupįnį eeja jee hegų.
As they were going along a whirlpool stood there.
ha'ų(h)ą(h)íregaja te horupínį eja je hegu
ha'ųhąhíregaja= the way they came there ha'ųhigają = the way he came there
Eegi hegų hiraicera rookra hiraicera hošewera howaraire hegų.
egi hegu hiraícera rokrá hiraícera (ho)šéwera (ho)waráire hegu
Hagoreižą eeja niižopoxižą eeja eeja hokawaire anąga hegų eegi wanoicgeąka eejaakšąną.
One time they went into a hole in the rock and that animal was lying there.
(ha)goréi(ž)ą eeja niižhopóxi(ž)ą eeja hokaíra anaga hegu egi wanoícge aka eja(h)akšąn(ą)
removed second "'eeja" at 3:21; also "hige" missing there? -- LP: Not sure if this is eeja or hige. Left as it is.
Hegų wiirapexjį nįįsge nąąǧire waʔųąkšąną hegų.
It was kind of anxiously waiting fearfully.
Hegų hegų hanąąc horoǧoǧoc hegų wanąxgų waʔųąkšąną hegų.
It was looking all around and listening to them.
hegu hegu hanáac horuǧóǧoc hegu wanáxgų (wa)'ųąkšąn(ą) hegu
Hagoreižą teʔe eeja hocįcįįknąąka eeja waajagi teʔeižą.
At one point it saw those boys.
(ha)goréi(ž)ą te'é eja (ho)cicį́įng ną́ąka eeja wajagí te'ei(ž)ą
Hegų eeja hegų hegų nįįžopox eeja teʔe eeja hegų xawanį jiikere hegų xawanį hegų.
There in the hole in the rock.
hegu eeja hegu hegu níižhopox eeja te'e eeja hegu xą́(w)ąni jikere hegu xą́(w)ąni hegu
Hegų hegų ruxaire hegų ruxe haraire hegų.
hegu hegu ruxáire hegu rux(e) (h)aráire hegu
Hagoreižą eeja nįge hiromąhą nįį nįįsge eeja nįge ąąjinąknąjee hajaire žeʔe heesge žeʔe eeja hegų ruxe harairegi eeja.
One time they went kind of upstream seemingly to shore and they saw it as they followed it there.
(ha)goréi(ž)ą eeja nigé hiromą́hąni (ni)ské eeja nigé ąąjínąk najé hajáire že'e (h)eské že'e eja rux(e) (h)aráiregi eeja
hiromą́hą = downstream, downwind ąąjínąk najé = he might have gotten out of the boat there (you're not so positive about it) (BO)
something missing after "'eeja" at 4:09 ("hegų ..."?) -- LP: Added hegų, but the rest is unclear.
Nįįš nįįšjeega hegų higicgis kerexjį hegų
They got there even with that rock.
higicgis kerexjį = he went very close to it higicgis = cut it off with
added "hegų" at the end -- LP: Ok.
Waʔųjee eegi hegų eeja hotiire anąga hegų hagoreižą niižopoxjeega hirahiireže hegų.
They climbed to where he was standing and arrived at that hole in the rock.
wa'ųje egi hegu eja hotír(e) anaga hegu (ha)goréi(ž)ą niižhopóx jega hiráhireže hegu
Hikišerejaaʔų hegų wanoicgeąka eeja hegų eeja waʔųireže tʼeehiire hegų tʼeehiire anąga.
There as they worked on the animal they killed it.
hikišére jaa'ų́ hegu wanóicg(e) aka eeja hegu eja wa'ų́įneže t'ehíre hegu t'ehír(e) anaga
Hanį hihinąp anąga hegų waʔira ųųsge hiʔųire anąga nįįšnąka eeja wagagaxire.
They took out the animal's blood and they used it to make multiple pictures on the rock.
haní hi(h)iną́p (a)naga wa'irá ųské hi'ų́įn(e) anaga niižną́ka eeja wagagáxire
wagagax = draw here and there (could mean graffiti? ) (BO) wagax = draw in one place
something missing after "'anąga"? -- LP: Added hegų.
